  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Bash</strong> the lemongrass (to release the juices) before slicing it down the middle</p>\r\n<p><strong>Separate</strong> the tough outer layers from the tender innards</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> the rice, 375ml <span class=\"text-danger\">(750ml)</span> water, outer lemongrass and salt (optional) to a pot with a matching lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Once</strong> boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook covered for 10-15 min or until the water is absorbed, checking occasionally</p>\r\n<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, cut each mushroom into wedges</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cut</strong> the pak choi into bite-size pieces, keeping the white and green seperate</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Peel</strong> the ginger by scraping the skin off with a teaspoon</p>\r\n<p><strong>Finely</strong> chop (or grate) the peeled ginger</p>\r\n<p><strong>Chop</strong> the reserved lemongrass innards finely</p>\r\n<p><strong>Slice</strong> the spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">(s)</span> finely, discarding the root end<span class=\"text-danger\">(s) </span></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Heat</strong> a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">(2 tbsp)</span> vegetable oil on a high heat</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> hot, add the mushroom with a pinch of salt and cook for 4-5 min or until caramelised, turning occasionally</p>\r\n<p>Tip: Allow your mushrooms to get quite dark - this gives them a smoky flavour!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, boil half a kettle</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> the sesame seeds to a pestle and mortar</p>\r\n<p><strong>Grind</strong> and bash the seeds with some force until you have a coarse powder</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the ginger and lemongrass innards and grind well</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">(2 tbsp)</span> boiled water, the soy sauce, mirin, 2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">(4 tsp)</span> sugar (preferably brown) and half the sesame oil</p>\r\n<p><strong>Grind</strong> thoroughly - this is your sesame sauce</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/486.-step-6-x400.jpg",
